<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 6:09PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A band of heavy lake effect snow will affect southern Geauga and
northeastern Cuyahoga Counties Until 700 PM EST....
At 603 PM EST, radar indicated a nearly stationary band of lake
effect snow extending from downtown Cleveland to Shaker Heights to
Chagrin Falls. Visibilities may drop to a half mile in snow with
quick accumulations making roads slick.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Snowfall rates of 1 inch per hour...
Roads becoming snow covered and slick...
Locations impacted include...
Cleveland, Lakewood, Cleveland Heights, Solon, Warrensville Heights,
South Russell, Highland Hills, Garfield Heights, Shaker Heights,
Maple Heights, South Euclid, Mayfield Heights, East Cleveland,
Lyndhurst, University Heights, Bedford, Beachwood, Brooklyn and
Bedford Heights.
&amp;&amp;
ODOT DMS  304, 307, 308, 310, 311, 319, 323, 324, 328, and 329.</description>
